{
  "page": "Heart of winter",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ea/The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg/350px-The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"204\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ea/The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg/525px-The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/ea/The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg/700px-The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_heart_of_winter_by_steves3511-da9uubp.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The heart of winter, by Stephen Najarian ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>heart of winter</b> is a place glimpsed by <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> in a dream while he is lying in a coma. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Heart_of_winter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Heart_of_winter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> is crippled after falling from the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Keep\" title=\"First Keep\">First Keep</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>. The comatose boy is visited by a <a href=\"/index.php/Three-eyed_crow\" title=\"Three-eyed crow\">three-eyed crow</a> during a dream, and he has visions of various places in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>. Bran looks <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>, and beyond the curtain of light (possibly an <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aurora\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Aurora\">Aurora Borealis</a>) at the edge of <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">the world</a>, into what he calls the heart of winter. What he sees there makes him cry. The crow tells Bran that he must live because winter is coming.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Bran then sees spires of ice rising up to impale him and the bodies of a thousand dreamers before him. The crow tells Bran that he must choose: fly or die. Bran spreads his arms and flies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Heart_of_winter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Finally he looked north. He saw the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> shining like blue crystal, and his bastard brother <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon</a> sleeping alone in a cold bed, his skin growing pale and hard as the memory of all warmth fled from him. And he looked <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">past the Wall</a>, past <a href=\"/index.php/Haunted_forest\" title=\"Haunted forest\">endless forests</a> cloaked in snow, past the <a href=\"/index.php/Frozen_shore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Frozen shore\">frozen shore</a> and the great blue-white rivers of ice and the <a href=\"/index.php/Land_of_Always_Winter\" title=\"Land of Always Winter\">dead plains</a> where nothing grew or lived. North and north and north he looked, to the curtain of light at the end of <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">the world</a>, and then beyond that curtain. He looked deep into the heart of winter, and then he cried out, afraid, and the heat of his tears burned on his cheeks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Crow</b>: Now you know. Now you know why you must live.<br />\n</p><p><b>Bran</b>: Why?<br />\n</p>\n<b>Crow</b>: Because winter is coming.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Three-eyed_crow\" title=\"Three-eyed crow\">Three-eyed crow</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Heart_of_winter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_17\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 17\">Chapter 17</a>, Bran III.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404192657\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.018 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.019 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 232/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8758/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2814/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1112/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1337/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    9.408      1 -total\n 70.08%    6.593      4 Template:Ref\n 36.72%    3.454      4 Template:Ref/core\n 29.47%    2.773      2 Template:Quote\n 17.82%    1.676      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:19562-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404192657 and revision id 323619\n -->\n",
